WEBVTT

1
00:00:10.083 --> 00:00:13.916
[woman breathing heavily]

2
00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:17.583
[intriguing music playing]

3
00:00:18.666 --> 00:00:21.833
INSPIRED BY A TRUE STORY

4
00:00:21.916 --> 00:00:27.250
[man] The laws of physics
nail the human race to the ground.

5
00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:33.583
Today. though.
you will be witnessing a miracle!

6
00:00:33.666 --> 00:00:36.625
A fine young woman. otherworldly.

7
00:00:36.708 --> 00:00:39.083
will rise up. dancing in the air.

8
00:00:39.166 --> 00:00:43.375
Because nature
bestowed a rare gift upon her.

9
00:00:43.458 --> 00:00:46.958
Miranda. sovereign of the air.

10
00:00:47.041 --> 00:00:50.458
tonight we ask of you. fly high.

11
00:00:50.541 --> 00:00:52.625
- [drumroll]
- Hup!

12
00:00:52.708 --> 00:00:53.958
Above us all!

13
00:00:54.958 --> 00:00:56.500
- [Miranda] Hup.
- [male trapezist grunts]

14
00:00:56.583 --> 00:00:59.958
[suspenseful music playing]

15
00:01:02.625 --> 00:01:03.625
[both] Hep.

16
00:01:09.666 --> 00:01:13.750
[audience cheering and applauding]

17
00:01:21.083 --> 00:01:23.291
[Miranda] Tell Paride to remove the nets.

18
00:01:25.166 --> 00:01:27.083
- Nets!
- [exhales deeply]

19
00:01:27.166 --> 00:01:30.208
["The Beginning of the End"
by Klergy & Valerie Broussard playing]

20
00:01:31.375 --> 00:01:33.625
<i>♪ Reckless behaviour… ♪</i>

21
00:01:33.708 --> 00:01:36.666
Attention now. ladies and gentlemen.

22
00:01:36.750 --> 00:01:41.333
Miranda has just given me notice
of something extraordinary.

23
00:01:41.416 --> 00:01:44.458
Just for you. just for tonight.

24
00:01:44.541 --> 00:01:50.041
she will fly for the very first time
without a net.

25
00:01:50.125 --> 00:01:52.000
[audience murmuring]

26
00:01:52.083 --> 00:01:54.291
<i>♪ When you close your eyes ♪</i>

27
00:01:54.375 --> 00:01:58.666
<i>♪ When you close your eyes ♪</i>

28
00:02:00.916 --> 00:02:04.000
<i>♪ What were we thinking? ♪</i>

29
00:02:04.083 --> 00:02:11.083
<i>♪ Back at the beginning</i>
<i>The beginning of the end? ♪</i>

30
00:02:12.125 --> 00:02:13.083
<i>♪ The end ♪</i>

31
00:02:13.166 --> 00:02:15.458
[breathes deeply]

32
00:02:17.208 --> 00:02:18.541
Hup!

33
00:02:18.625 --> 00:02:20.416
[music builds]

34
00:02:22.916 --> 00:02:23.958
[song intensifies]

35
00:02:24.041 --> 00:02:30.250
<i>♪ Oh. oh </i>♪

36
00:02:35.833 --> 00:02:36.791
[song stops]

37
00:02:36.875 --> 00:02:39.958
[dramatic sting]

38
00:02:40.041 --> 00:02:41.375
<i>♪ The end ♪</i>

39
00:02:41.458 --> 00:02:42.541
[audience screaming]

40
00:02:42.625 --> 00:02:45.750
[dramatic note plays]

41
00:02:52.833 --> 00:02:55.958
[theme music playing]

42
00:02:59.166 --> 00:03:02.750
THE LAW ACCORDING TO LIDIA POËT

43
00:03:05.500 --> 00:03:06.791
[music fades]

44
00:03:06.875 --> 00:03:08.208
[birds chirping]

45
00:03:16.458 --> 00:03:21.041
{\an8}Men often talk about women
as if they were essentially fragile.

46
00:03:21.916 --> 00:03:24.291
{\an8}They deny their capacity for science.

47
00:03:24.375 --> 00:03:28.291
{\an8}their intellect.
socially. politically. their strength.

48
00:03:28.375 --> 00:03:31.791
{\an8}and. forgive me.
but it is not me who says so.

49
00:03:31.875 --> 00:03:35.291
{\an8}They themselves acknowledge it.
with their legislation.

50
00:03:36.791 --> 00:03:39.625
{\an8}But if they really believed
what they said.

51
00:03:39.708 --> 00:03:42.791
{\an8}they wouldn't feel so threatened
by us women. right?

52
00:03:43.916 --> 00:03:47.500
{\an8}If we really were fragile and inadequate.

53
00:03:47.583 --> 00:03:51.041
{\an8}then there would be no need to keep us
under constant forced protection.

54
00:03:52.041 --> 00:03:55.125
{\an8}- Yes?
- Dr Poët. allow me. please.

55
00:03:55.208 --> 00:03:57.708
{\an8}- What you say is wonderful.
- But?

56
00:03:57.791 --> 00:04:01.958
{\an8}But. indeed. I think your example suggests

57
00:04:02.041 --> 00:04:06.208
{\an8}that in order for one
to exercise her liberty continuously.

58
00:04:06.291 --> 00:04:10.333
{\an8}a woman needs
to have a… gentleman's protection.

59
00:04:10.416 --> 00:04:12.416
{\an8}like you need your brother. Deputy Poët.

60
00:04:14.375 --> 00:04:17.250
{\an8}I am very grateful to my brother

61
00:04:17.333 --> 00:04:19.375
{\an8}for everything he's done for me.

62
00:04:19.458 --> 00:04:21.250
{\an8}But the truth is something else.

63
00:04:21.875 --> 00:04:26.000
{\an8}Namely. that if I'm here in this room
with you all today.

64
00:04:26.083 --> 00:04:31.208
{\an8}and a law that I wrote is in Parliament
ready to be discussed and voted.

65
00:04:31.291 --> 00:04:33.541
{\an8}it is mainly thanks to one woman.

66
00:04:33.625 --> 00:04:36.166
{\an8}[whimsical music playing]

67
00:04:37.250 --> 00:04:40.166
{\an8}<i>When I met her.</i>
<i>she was working in a tobacco factory.</i>

68
00:04:40.791 --> 00:04:43.666
{\an8}And I had just run away
from my father's house.

69
00:04:43.750 --> 00:04:46.666
{\an8}I was alone.
and I was completely unprepared for life.

70
00:04:46.750 --> 00:04:49.625
{\an8}<i>I even lacked money for food.</i>

71
00:04:49.708 --> 00:04:51.791
{\an8}And the first time she spoke to me.
she said.

72
00:04:51.875 --> 00:04:54.458
{\an8}"You've never worked a day in your life.
have you?"

73
00:04:55.375 --> 00:04:57.708
{\an8}She offered me a place to stay.

74
00:04:57.791 --> 00:05:00.958
{\an8}and she even helped me pay for university

75
00:05:01.041 --> 00:05:04.041
{\an8}without asking for anything
but a friend to stand by her side.

76
00:05:04.125 --> 00:05:05.291
[woman] Pardon me. sir.

77
00:05:05.375 --> 00:05:07.833
[sighs] Were you not told
the carriages with oil lanterns

78
00:05:07.916 --> 00:05:09.750
have been temporarily prohibited?

79
00:05:09.833 --> 00:05:10.833
You see. just there. look.

80
00:05:10.916 --> 00:05:12.875
There was an accident
at the corner of Via Po.

81
00:05:12.958 --> 00:05:15.125
I'd never forgive myself
if yours was taken.

82
00:05:15.208 --> 00:05:18.250
- Appreciate it. Thank you so much!
- Miss! Miss! Miss!

83
00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:19.875
[Lidia] So…

84
00:05:20.666 --> 00:05:23.708
it is true.
maybe the time has not yet arrived

85
00:05:24.416 --> 00:05:27.750
for a woman to be able
to do without those men

86
00:05:27.833 --> 00:05:30.833
who hold the ability for change
in their hands.

87
00:05:32.875 --> 00:05:36.083
But just take a look at the woman
who sits next to you

88
00:05:37.041 --> 00:05:39.708
and join her in the same battle

89
00:05:40.250 --> 00:05:44.208
so that the voice of one
becomes the voice of all.

90
00:05:44.833 --> 00:05:46.875
And. above all.
so that it reaches the ears

91
00:05:46.958 --> 00:05:48.583
of those who do not want to listen.

92
00:05:49.125 --> 00:05:53.083
- So… [chuckles]
- [all applauding]

93
00:05:53.166 --> 00:05:56.083
[uplifting music playing]

94
00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:04.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

95
00:06:05.083 --> 00:06:07.083
[birds chirping]

96
00:06:19.875 --> 00:06:22.791
Well… have you been waiting long?

97
00:06:22.875 --> 00:06:24.000
Only nine years.

98
00:06:24.083 --> 00:06:25.958
[both chuckling]

99
00:06:26.958 --> 00:06:27.791
You're…

100
00:06:27.875 --> 00:06:29.375
- A bit older?
- [woman] Beautiful.

101
00:06:29.458 --> 00:06:30.583
[both chuckle fondly]

102
00:06:30.666 --> 00:06:32.833
[gentle music playing]

103
00:06:33.791 --> 00:06:35.583
[inhales] I missed you.

104
00:06:35.666 --> 00:06:36.791
[woman] Me too.

105
00:06:36.875 --> 00:06:39.041
[music crescendos. fades abruptly]

106
00:06:39.875 --> 00:06:43.083
Can we talk seriously?
When will you introduce me?

107
00:06:43.166 --> 00:06:44.583
[Lidia chuckles]

108
00:06:44.666 --> 00:06:47.083
- Who?
- Don't be coy. The prosecutor.

109
00:06:47.166 --> 00:06:48.333
Shh.

110
00:06:48.416 --> 00:06:50.666
- It's nothing official.
- It's not?

111
00:06:50.750 --> 00:06:52.125
No. we can't talk about it.

112
00:06:52.208 --> 00:06:54.583
- [man] Stop right there!
- Does he know you'll break his heart?

113
00:06:54.666 --> 00:06:55.750
I actually like him a lot.

114
00:06:55.833 --> 00:06:57.750
- Mummy?
- [man] Stop! Carabinieri!

115
00:06:57.833 --> 00:06:59.250
Thank you. Mila. they're great!

116
00:06:59.333 --> 00:07:00.791
- [Lidia cries out]
- Careful. Lidia!

117
00:07:00.875 --> 00:07:02.250
You filthy pig! Leave me alone!

118
00:07:02.333 --> 00:07:03.750
[tense music playing]

119
00:07:03.833 --> 00:07:05.041
- [carabiniere grunts]
- [groans]

120
00:07:06.208 --> 00:07:07.791
No. stop. Come back!

121
00:07:08.500 --> 00:07:09.500
[cuffs clicking]

122
00:07:10.333 --> 00:07:12.416
Do you realise that's an abuse of power?

123
00:07:12.500 --> 00:07:14.208
Step aside. ma'am.
This woman killed a girl.

124
00:07:14.291 --> 00:07:17.583
- That is no excuse for smashing her face.
- I didn't do anything.

125
00:07:17.666 --> 00:07:18.708
[carabiniere] Move!

126
00:07:19.375 --> 00:07:20.458
Walk.

127
00:07:22.083 --> 00:07:25.291
[dramatic music playing]

128
00:07:26.791 --> 00:07:30.000
Ask for Enrico Poët. He's a lawyer.

129
00:07:30.083 --> 00:07:33.333
- Right. Now she wants a lawyer.
- Enrico Poët. He sits in Parliament!

130
00:07:35.458 --> 00:07:38.041
- Lidia. your dress has been torn.
- That's the least of my worries.

131
00:07:38.125 --> 00:07:40.000
No. it's really badly torn.

132
00:07:40.083 --> 00:07:42.583
Oh. fuck. Oh…

133
00:07:42.666 --> 00:07:45.791
Sorry. dear.
You must never use words like that. Never.

134
00:07:48.666 --> 00:07:51.166
Come on. nothing to see here. Move along.

135
00:07:51.250 --> 00:07:53.083
- They do make my blood boil.
- I know.

136
00:07:53.166 --> 00:07:55.000
Do you know how many times
they arrest people

137
00:07:55.083 --> 00:07:56.666
without a single shred of evidence?

138
00:07:56.750 --> 00:07:57.791
There. done.

139
00:07:58.583 --> 00:08:00.208
- [Lidia] Thank you.
- Perfect.

140
00:08:00.958 --> 00:08:02.541
So you'll stay here with us tonight.

141
00:08:02.625 --> 00:08:05.333
No. our things are at the guesthouse.
We couldn't possibly stay.

142
00:08:05.416 --> 00:08:08.125
I'll lend you something.
We have a house with 16 rooms available.

143
00:08:08.208 --> 00:08:09.166
Let's use them.

144
00:08:09.250 --> 00:08:11.666
- Shouldn't we first inform Enrico?
- [Lidia] No.

145
00:08:11.750 --> 00:08:13.291
Sure about that?

146
00:08:13.375 --> 00:08:15.416
He'll be back tomorrow with Teresa.

147
00:08:16.333 --> 00:08:19.291
- And we haven't toasted yet.
- Can I drink it too?

148
00:08:19.375 --> 00:08:22.083
Uh. Mila. perhaps you could
in the next ten years.

149
00:08:22.166 --> 00:08:24.333
Why don't you take a look
around the house?

150
00:08:24.416 --> 00:08:26.750
So you can see
how these electorates reside.

151
00:08:26.833 --> 00:08:28.625
Deputies are boring.

152
00:08:28.708 --> 00:08:30.583
- Well…
- Yes. that's true.

153
00:08:30.666 --> 00:08:34.333
But I remember their daughters.
They all have dolls to play with.

154
00:08:34.416 --> 00:08:36.750
And if you go to my niece's room.
they're all still there.

155
00:08:36.833 --> 00:08:39.375
She lives in Paris now.
so we won't tell her you found them.

156
00:08:39.458 --> 00:08:41.041
Down the long corridor.

157
00:08:42.333 --> 00:08:44.333
[footsteps departing]

158
00:08:47.708 --> 00:08:49.750
[inhales] To us. my friend.

159
00:08:53.833 --> 00:08:56.083
I need to confess something.

160
00:08:56.166 --> 00:08:58.250
[pensive music playing]

161
00:08:58.333 --> 00:09:00.833
I actually came here
to visit you for a reason.

162
00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:06.291
Unfortunately. I'm in need of a loan.

163
00:09:10.916 --> 00:09:12.083
All right.

164
00:09:12.166 --> 00:09:15.083
No. it's a substantial amount of money.

165
00:09:15.166 --> 00:09:18.041
I've accumulated some debts that
my husband knows nothing about. and…

166
00:09:18.125 --> 00:09:19.125
How much?

167
00:09:21.458 --> 00:09:23.875
- 2.000 lire.
- [Lidia exhales]

168
00:09:23.958 --> 00:09:25.916
I know.
I'll pay it all back. rest assured.

169
00:09:26.000 --> 00:09:28.958
That's not the problem. Grazia.
I just don't have it.

170
00:09:30.583 --> 00:09:31.708
I don't.

171
00:09:34.750 --> 00:09:37.250
- Enrico can't help us?
- [Lidia] Enrico…

172
00:09:39.541 --> 00:09:41.416
I can try and talk to him. but…

173
00:09:46.958 --> 00:09:49.000
We'll figure something out.

174
00:09:49.083 --> 00:09:50.208
Don't worry.

175
00:09:52.125 --> 00:09:55.208
Tell me. how did you ever… how did you…

176
00:09:55.291 --> 00:09:57.000
- [Mila] Can I play with this?
- [gasps]

177
00:09:57.083 --> 00:09:58.125
Oh. sure.

178
00:09:58.875 --> 00:10:01.416
But first. you have to come with me.

179
00:10:01.500 --> 00:10:03.125
I want to show you something.

180
00:10:04.333 --> 00:10:09.125
Because you'll find out
that your mother… is a fabulous dancer.

181
00:10:09.208 --> 00:10:10.291
No.

182
00:10:10.375 --> 00:10:12.500
- [Lidia] And now we'll show you.
- [Grazia] No.

183
00:10:12.583 --> 00:10:13.583
Oh. yes.

184
00:10:13.666 --> 00:10:16.166
- And you can't turn us down.
- [Grazia] No. Lidia. please.

185
00:10:16.250 --> 00:10:18.708
- [Grazia] Oh gosh… [chuckles]
- [roller organ playing]

186
00:10:18.791 --> 00:10:22.291
All right. Just like this.
One hand here. the other one here.

187
00:10:22.375 --> 00:10:26.541
And spin. spin. spin. spin.
faster. faster. faster. faster. faster…

188
00:10:26.625 --> 00:10:27.750
[Grazia] All right.

189
00:10:27.833 --> 00:10:30.125
I'll take the lead. if you'll allow?

190
00:10:31.166 --> 00:10:33.750
[roller organ playing waltz]

191
00:10:33.833 --> 00:10:36.208
[all laughing]

192
00:10:41.375 --> 00:10:43.708
- Oh my. you're so graceful.
- [Grazia] No. I…

193
00:10:43.791 --> 00:10:45.291
[Lidia] Spectacular!

194
00:10:45.375 --> 00:10:47.750
- Oh no. no. no. no! I can't!
- [Lidia squeals]

195
00:10:47.833 --> 00:10:49.833
[both laughing and screaming]

196
00:10:50.791 --> 00:10:55.041
Wait. wait! My…
I believe my skirt ripped again!

197
00:10:56.875 --> 00:10:59.708
- Oh.
- That's enough for today.

198
00:10:59.791 --> 00:11:02.041
- [Lidia ] No. Mila. shall we keep going?
- No. I'm done now.

199
00:11:02.125 --> 00:11:03.583
- [Lidia] Yes! She said yes.
- Oh gosh!

200
00:11:03.666 --> 00:11:07.041
She said yes. Faster. faster!

201
00:11:07.125 --> 00:11:08.291
Help!

202
00:11:08.375 --> 00:11:10.750
[both laughing and squealing]

203
00:11:10.833 --> 00:11:12.041
[door opens]

204
00:11:14.125 --> 00:11:17.500
[music distorts. stops]

205
00:11:17.583 --> 00:11:18.541
[Lidia] Enrico.

206
00:11:19.708 --> 00:11:22.750
Teresa. Weren't you supposed
to come back tomorrow?

207
00:11:23.375 --> 00:11:26.208
May I ask you
why you're in your underwear. Lidia?

208
00:11:26.291 --> 00:11:28.291
- [Grazia laughing quietly]
- Oh. well…

209
00:11:28.875 --> 00:11:30.250
[Teresa] Don't get us wrong. Lidia.

210
00:11:30.333 --> 00:11:33.083
We are very happy
that you found this friend of yours again.

211
00:11:33.166 --> 00:11:37.041
But since she's sleeping at our house.
we would just like to know who she is.

212
00:11:37.833 --> 00:11:39.208
Enrico is now in Parliament.

213
00:11:39.291 --> 00:11:41.750
and he can't have random people
in the house.

214
00:11:41.833 --> 00:11:44.083
Actually. Enrico knows perfectly well
who she is.

215
00:11:44.166 --> 00:11:46.666
- He's pretending not to remember.
- I've never seen her in my life.

216
00:11:46.750 --> 00:11:49.583
If it wasn't for her. I would never have
finished university. You know it.

217
00:11:49.666 --> 00:11:51.666
So you are in debt to her?

218
00:11:55.916 --> 00:11:58.625
[sombre music playing]

219
00:11:58.708 --> 00:12:00.375
[winces]

220
00:12:01.875 --> 00:12:03.791
- No.
- [Teresa] Hm.

221
00:12:07.750 --> 00:12:11.291
[inhales] Anyway. Enrico.
I need an advance on my next pay cheques.

222
00:12:12.500 --> 00:12:13.333
All right.

223
00:12:14.083 --> 00:12:16.125
- About 2.000 lire.
- [Enrico coughs]

224
00:12:17.750 --> 00:12:20.583
Lidia. do you really know
what the house costs are?

225
00:12:20.666 --> 00:12:21.500
[scoffs]

226
00:12:21.583 --> 00:12:23.291
Maybe not.
as you don't contribute to them.

227
00:12:23.375 --> 00:12:26.458
[Teresa] What Enrico means is that
being a deputy costs a lot of money.

228
00:12:26.541 --> 00:12:28.875
and it certainly wasn't his ambition.

229
00:12:32.125 --> 00:12:34.250
[Enrico] Can I at least ask you
what you need it for?

230
00:12:35.333 --> 00:12:37.333
[cutlery clattering softly]

231
00:12:37.416 --> 00:12:39.333
So that's… no.

232
00:12:39.416 --> 00:12:42.000
- [Lidia] I was simply asking a question.
- [Enrico] I gave an answer.

233
00:12:42.083 --> 00:12:44.416
Don't think I'm not helping
cover the expenses of this house.

234
00:12:44.500 --> 00:12:46.666
Next time you need
a closing statement reviewed.

235
00:12:46.750 --> 00:12:48.000
you should ask someone else.

236
00:12:48.083 --> 00:12:49.541
- [Grazia] Good morning.
- Good morning.

237
00:12:49.625 --> 00:12:50.875
[Teresa] Good morning.

238
00:12:51.500 --> 00:12:53.708
Mila. sweetheart.

239
00:12:53.791 --> 00:12:55.833
That doll is very fragile.

240
00:12:55.916 --> 00:12:57.625
- Oh. sorry. it's…
- Don't worry.

241
00:12:57.708 --> 00:13:01.083
- If you give it to me. I'll put it away.
- Please. have a seat.

242
00:13:01.166 --> 00:13:02.083
Thank you.

243
00:13:02.166 --> 00:13:04.375
[Enrico] Help yourselves.
There's a bit of everything.

244
00:13:04.458 --> 00:13:06.541
Tea with milk. croissant. <i>chocolat chaud.</i>

245
00:13:06.625 --> 00:13:08.291
- [chuckles]
- [bell dings]

246
00:13:08.375 --> 00:13:09.791
[Enrico] No. no. no. please.

247
00:13:09.875 --> 00:13:11.708
Let me. Albertina. <i>Excusez-moi.</i>

248
00:13:11.791 --> 00:13:13.166
<i>De rien.</i>

249
00:13:14.958 --> 00:13:18.375
[Lidia and Grazia laughing]

250
00:13:19.750 --> 00:13:21.250
- [Lidia] Did you sleep well?
- I did.

251
00:13:22.916 --> 00:13:26.416
- Did you… talk to him?
- Yes.

252
00:13:26.958 --> 00:13:30.166
- It's a bit of a complicated time.
- [Grazia] Mm.

253
00:13:30.250 --> 00:13:33.125
Maybe if you could wait
a couple more days…

254
00:13:33.208 --> 00:13:35.416
[tense music playing]

255
00:13:35.500 --> 00:13:37.083
You can't? You're not able to?

256
00:13:37.166 --> 00:13:40.375
No. I told my husband we'd be back today.
so it's imperative that we…

257
00:13:40.458 --> 00:13:42.166
[Lidia] Can't you write to him?

258
00:13:42.250 --> 00:13:44.083
Tell him you're staying a little longer.

259
00:13:44.791 --> 00:13:46.583
So we spend some time together.

260
00:13:48.375 --> 00:13:49.458
I couldn't. Lidia.

261
00:13:49.541 --> 00:13:53.250
- [Enrico] Lidia!
- [Lidia sighs in exasperation]

262
00:13:53.916 --> 00:13:57.375
- We'll talk about it later. Don't go away.
- [Grazia] Mm-hmm. No.

263
00:13:58.291 --> 00:14:01.208
[footsteps departing]

264
00:14:01.291 --> 00:14:03.875
[music fades]

265
00:14:14.166 --> 00:14:17.916
Lidia. these nice gentlemen
had my business card.

266
00:14:18.000 --> 00:14:19.541
I take it this is your doing?

267
00:14:19.625 --> 00:14:20.625
[Lidia] Mm-hmm.

268
00:14:20.708 --> 00:14:23.125
- I'm Paride. from the Circus Laforêt.
- Hello.

269
00:14:23.208 --> 00:14:26.291
Yesterday. one of our artists
was arrested and beaten.

270
00:14:26.375 --> 00:14:28.625
- Her name is Lorena Guerri.
- [Lidia] Of course.

271
00:14:28.708 --> 00:14:32.333
But please. make yourselves comfortable.
My brother will be very happy to help you.

272
00:14:32.416 --> 00:14:33.250
Hm?

273
00:14:34.500 --> 00:14:39.291
Last Sunday. during the matinée.
Miranda Laforêt performed on the trapeze.

274
00:14:39.375 --> 00:14:43.708
without a safety net.
and fell from a height of nine metres.

275
00:14:43.791 --> 00:14:45.916
At first. it seemed like an accident.

276
00:14:46.000 --> 00:14:48.791
but then the coroner found
on the thigh of the victim

277
00:14:48.875 --> 00:14:51.333
signs of frequent injections.

278
00:14:51.416 --> 00:14:53.791
So it transpired that your client

279
00:14:53.875 --> 00:14:56.125
regularly injected the victim
with analgesics.

280
00:14:56.208 --> 00:14:58.125
- [knocking on door]
- [man] Come in.

281
00:14:58.916 --> 00:15:01.625
Good morning. Your Honour.
Apologies for my tardiness.

282
00:15:02.750 --> 00:15:04.958
Turin's topography is quite mysterious.

283
00:15:05.041 --> 00:15:07.375
Have you met the new Royal Prosecutor?

284
00:15:07.458 --> 00:15:11.083
- Giovanni Cantamessa. I'm honoured.
- Advocate Enrico Poët. The honour is mine.

285
00:15:11.166 --> 00:15:12.791
[intriguing string music playing]

286
00:15:12.875 --> 00:15:16.666
And tell me. to whom do we owe
the presence of this beautiful lady?

287
00:15:17.666 --> 00:15:21.375
[exhales] This is Dr Lidia Poët.

288
00:15:21.458 --> 00:15:25.375
my assistant in legal matters.
and my sister.

289
00:15:26.000 --> 00:15:28.541
Did you hear that Mr Fourneau
was appointed Prosecutor General

290
00:15:28.625 --> 00:15:30.416
of the Court of Assizes?

291
00:15:30.500 --> 00:15:32.166
Yes. indeed. we heard.

292
00:15:32.250 --> 00:15:34.583
He won't be missed.
thanks to Mr Cantamessa.

293
00:15:34.666 --> 00:15:35.500
Ooh.

294
00:15:35.583 --> 00:15:37.375
He was very thorough
in this specific case.

295
00:15:37.958 --> 00:15:39.791
It was my duty. Your Honour.

296
00:15:39.875 --> 00:15:41.291
I had the circus wagons searched.

297
00:15:41.375 --> 00:15:44.166
and interrogated the witnesses
and collected their testimonies.

298
00:15:44.250 --> 00:15:47.833
and. as the judge
has probably already told you.

299
00:15:47.916 --> 00:15:51.166
I tracked down the syringe
and the vial used for the injection.

300
00:15:51.250 --> 00:15:54.583
And I took the liberty of having
the substance in the vial analysed.

301
00:15:54.666 --> 00:15:57.416
and. as you can see from the report.

302
00:15:58.083 --> 00:16:01.000
the results came back. and it turned out
to be a soporific substance

303
00:16:01.083 --> 00:16:03.083
capable of knocking out a horse.

304
00:16:03.166 --> 00:16:06.500
Why did you rule out
the possibility of a mistake?

305
00:16:06.583 --> 00:16:08.125
[intriguing music continues]

306
00:16:08.208 --> 00:16:10.291
I don't quite get the question.
Counsellor.

307
00:16:11.541 --> 00:16:14.833
[inhales sharply] We were wondering
why you immediately

308
00:16:14.916 --> 00:16:19.791
thought of a premeditated murder.
and not of a mistake made in good faith.

309
00:16:19.875 --> 00:16:23.000
Ah. of course. a mistake
is always possible. You're right.

310
00:16:23.083 --> 00:16:27.166
Strange. though. that this mistake
was made by Mrs Lorena Guerri.

311
00:16:27.250 --> 00:16:29.708
who is married to Mr Rubino Guerri.

312
00:16:29.791 --> 00:16:32.416
who is this person here.
and who. as you can see.

313
00:16:32.500 --> 00:16:37.375
appears in all the circus advertisements
together with the victim.

314
00:16:37.458 --> 00:16:40.583
Clearly in… lascivious poses.

315
00:16:40.666 --> 00:16:44.583
So. in your opinion.
the motive would be… jealousy?

316
00:16:46.125 --> 00:16:50.875
Uh. well. as we know. Counsellor.
people only kill for two reasons.

317
00:16:50.958 --> 00:16:54.250
If it's not for money. it's for love.

318
00:16:55.333 --> 00:16:57.916
Miranda lost both her parents
when she was six.

319
00:16:58.750 --> 00:17:00.250
She was like my sister.

320
00:17:00.333 --> 00:17:03.916
My husband taught her the trapeze.
And you're telling me that I was jealous?

321
00:17:04.000 --> 00:17:06.458
Oh. unfortunately.
the prosecutor is convinced

322
00:17:06.541 --> 00:17:09.416
that there was something less spiritual
between your husband and Miranda.

323
00:17:09.500 --> 00:17:11.125
And how exactly would he know?

324
00:17:11.208 --> 00:17:13.750
He's from the South.
They see jealousy everywhere there.

325
00:17:13.833 --> 00:17:15.250
Now. without wanting to generalise…

326
00:17:15.333 --> 00:17:18.458
The problem is that you used this syringe
and this particular vial.

327
00:17:18.541 --> 00:17:21.625
Yes. I gave her an injection
before the show. So what?

328
00:17:21.708 --> 00:17:24.541
She suffered from back pain.
You can ask my husband.

329
00:17:24.625 --> 00:17:28.083
He'll tell you that Miranda insisted.
She wanted to perform no matter what.

330
00:17:28.166 --> 00:17:31.083
[Enrico] Are you absolutely sure
you didn't use the wrong medicine?

331
00:17:31.166 --> 00:17:32.458
How could I get it wrong. sir?

332
00:17:33.041 --> 00:17:35.958
The vial has a red label.
I've been using that one every day.

333
00:17:36.833 --> 00:17:39.250
- Are you sure he's the best you've got?
- Excuse me. how dare…

334
00:17:39.333 --> 00:17:43.416
Yes. he is. What he means is that maybe
someone who knew about these injections

335
00:17:43.500 --> 00:17:47.416
could have simply replaced the painkiller
with the sleeping agent.

336
00:17:47.500 --> 00:17:48.625
[sombre music playing]

337
00:17:48.708 --> 00:17:50.916
Someone who wanted to kill Miranda?

338
00:17:51.458 --> 00:17:52.458
Why?

339
00:17:54.416 --> 00:17:56.625
No. Counsellor. [scoffs]

340
00:17:56.708 --> 00:17:59.000
The point is they hate us
because we're Gypsies.

341
00:17:59.083 --> 00:18:01.250
The prosecutor made himself
look good in the papers.

342
00:18:01.333 --> 00:18:04.000
Well. I sincerely hope
that is not the case.

343
00:18:04.083 --> 00:18:07.375
And if it is. they'll crawl in
on their knees and apologise to you.

344
00:18:07.458 --> 00:18:08.875
I promise.

345
00:18:08.958 --> 00:18:10.541
[sombre music continues]

346
00:18:10.625 --> 00:18:13.666
[Teresa] It'll be just the three of us.
and Ms Marianna.

347
00:18:14.250 --> 00:18:16.083
Unfortunately.
I haven't heard from my brother.

348
00:18:16.166 --> 00:18:19.250
- [Albertina] Sorry to hear that. ma'am.
- [Teresa] Well. it doesn't matter.

349
00:18:20.666 --> 00:18:22.666
- Forgive me. dear.
- [Grazia gasps]

350
00:18:22.750 --> 00:18:25.833
I didn't quite understand how long
you plan to stay here with us after all.

351
00:18:25.916 --> 00:18:27.625
[Grazia] Oh. we'll leave…

352
00:18:27.708 --> 00:18:28.916
- We'll be leaving…
- Oh. perfect.

353
00:18:29.000 --> 00:18:31.791
Because my daughter is arriving
on Good Friday. and she'll need the room.

354
00:18:31.875 --> 00:18:32.958
[Grazia] Mm-hmm.

355
00:18:35.083 --> 00:18:36.250
[exhales shakily]

356
00:18:36.333 --> 00:18:40.041
[pensive music playing]

357
00:18:59.666 --> 00:19:01.541
- [knocking on door]
- [Fourneau] Come in.

358
00:19:05.666 --> 00:19:06.916
[Fourneau] Ms Poët.

359
00:19:08.375 --> 00:19:10.208
I'm surprised to see you.

360
00:19:10.750 --> 00:19:13.500
Excuse me. I was looking
for the Prosecutor General

361
00:19:13.583 --> 00:19:15.291
of the Court of Assizes.

362
00:19:15.375 --> 00:19:18.625
Then you'll have to come back in two weeks
when the appointment will be official.

363
00:19:18.708 --> 00:19:21.625
because I'm only here
to arrange his books for him.

364
00:19:21.708 --> 00:19:23.666
[wistful music playing softly]

365
00:19:23.750 --> 00:19:24.875
[Lidia chuckles]

366
00:19:26.958 --> 00:19:28.750
Getting a bit anxious?

367
00:19:29.458 --> 00:19:30.375
Could be worse.

368
00:19:31.250 --> 00:19:35.458
Yes. At most.
I'll miss the field investigations a bit.

369
00:19:36.458 --> 00:19:41.166
But the real problem is that wearing
a gown would be utterly ridiculous.

370
00:19:41.250 --> 00:19:42.958
- [chuckles]
- [Fourneau] Yes.

371
00:19:45.000 --> 00:19:47.125
Would it embarrass you
if I came to your first hearing?

372
00:19:47.208 --> 00:19:48.458
No.

373
00:19:48.541 --> 00:19:51.000
No. I mean. it wouldn't be embarrassing.

374
00:19:51.875 --> 00:19:55.666
But I think that…
it's better if you don't.

375
00:19:56.291 --> 00:20:01.333
In order not to give rise to. uh… gossip.

376
00:20:01.416 --> 00:20:02.458
That's all.

377
00:20:03.000 --> 00:20:05.833
Maybe it's best you get
the keys to the door. then.

378
00:20:06.541 --> 00:20:08.000
At your order.

379
00:20:15.250 --> 00:20:16.333
How's your friend?

380
00:20:16.416 --> 00:20:19.666
What you said about her in your lecture
made me want to meet her.

381
00:20:19.750 --> 00:20:22.916
I'll introduce you.
She… she should stay a few more days.

382
00:20:23.000 --> 00:20:27.666
Just long enough to solve some. uh.
financial issues she has. Uh…

383
00:20:28.333 --> 00:20:30.125
- Can I do something?
- No.

384
00:20:32.125 --> 00:20:33.125
No.

385
00:20:36.666 --> 00:20:38.333
[exhales] This arrived yesterday.

386
00:20:38.416 --> 00:20:40.458
[poignant music playing]

387
00:20:40.541 --> 00:20:43.250
The doctor who operated on me sent it.

388
00:20:43.333 --> 00:20:47.458
[clicks tongue] And it's very thin.
so clearly it's not a book.

389
00:20:48.250 --> 00:20:50.375
If it's not a book.
I thought it might be a letter.

390
00:20:50.458 --> 00:20:52.708
- But if a doctor sends you a letter…
- Want me to open it?

391
00:20:54.750 --> 00:20:57.041
Please. Yes.

392
00:20:59.708 --> 00:21:02.083
[sombre music playing]

393
00:21:03.750 --> 00:21:06.708
[paper rustling]

394
00:21:17.583 --> 00:21:18.916
What does it say?

395
00:21:21.166 --> 00:21:22.500
Is it serious?

396
00:21:24.208 --> 00:21:25.041
Lidia.

397
00:21:25.750 --> 00:21:28.083
You're in the history of medicine.

398
00:21:28.750 --> 00:21:31.000
- [Fourneau chuckles softly]
- Look.

399
00:21:31.083 --> 00:21:34.583
[emotional music playing]

400
00:21:34.666 --> 00:21:37.375
- Look at my brain. mm?
- [Lidia] Mm.

401
00:21:39.416 --> 00:21:42.875
[chuckles softly] "Fact is.
symptoms are no longer present here".

402
00:21:44.750 --> 00:21:45.750
[chuckles softly]

403
00:21:46.250 --> 00:21:47.458
You're alive.

404
00:21:48.041 --> 00:21:49.416
You're well.

405
00:21:50.000 --> 00:21:51.500
One could say handsome.

406
00:21:56.166 --> 00:21:58.583
I would never have had the operation
without you.

407
00:21:58.666 --> 00:21:59.916
Never.

408
00:22:02.291 --> 00:22:04.333
You're so romantic.

409
00:22:04.416 --> 00:22:05.583
My young Werther.

410
00:22:05.666 --> 00:22:07.166
[knocking on door]

411
00:22:09.375 --> 00:22:11.416
{\an8}THANKS FOR EVERYTHING
I COULDN'T WAIT FOR YOU - GRAZIA

412
00:22:11.500 --> 00:22:12.833
{\an8}[Enrico] Grazia left this morning.

413
00:22:12.916 --> 00:22:13.791
I wasn't home.

414
00:22:13.875 --> 00:22:16.750
but I'm sure Teresa did
everything she could to stop her.

415
00:22:16.833 --> 00:22:18.208
What do you mean she left? Why?

416
00:22:18.291 --> 00:22:21.541
Anyway. it is fortunate.
because we have another visitor.

417
00:22:21.625 --> 00:22:24.375
- No. no. no.
- No. no. a nice visitor. I assure you.

418
00:22:24.458 --> 00:22:26.750
A wonderful. special surprise.

419
00:22:26.833 --> 00:22:30.333
A person who…
who never shows their face in Rome.

420
00:22:30.416 --> 00:22:33.208
but who decided to come visit us at home.

421
00:22:34.750 --> 00:22:37.250
[gentle music playing]

422
00:22:39.708 --> 00:22:40.791
[Lidia] Jacopo.

423
00:22:40.875 --> 00:22:41.916
[Jacopo] Lidia.

424
00:22:43.750 --> 00:22:45.958
- [Lidia] Welcome back.
- Thank you.

425
00:22:47.791 --> 00:22:49.833
Congratulations. You never wrote to me.

426
00:22:49.916 --> 00:22:52.041
- Oh. but I do write for my newspaper.
- [Lidia] Ah.

427
00:22:52.125 --> 00:22:54.000
Don't you get <i>Il Martello </i>in Turin?

428
00:22:54.083 --> 00:22:55.708
We don't read that here.

429
00:22:55.791 --> 00:22:57.416
[Jacopo laughing]

430
00:22:59.083 --> 00:23:01.083
[Lidia] You are Consuelo…

431
00:23:01.166 --> 00:23:03.708
Consuelo Vega del Carmen.
Nice to meet you. Lidia.

432
00:23:03.791 --> 00:23:05.958
Oh. pleasure.

433
00:23:06.041 --> 00:23:07.666
[Jacopo] We met
at the Opera House in Rome.

434
00:23:07.750 --> 00:23:12.166
I was in the audience. and she simply
couldn't resist my alluring magnetism.

435
00:23:12.250 --> 00:23:13.458
Your magnetism.

436
00:23:13.541 --> 00:23:14.791
- That one. yes.
- It's all true.

437
00:23:14.875 --> 00:23:17.791
This treacherous man made me
lose any sense of reality.

438
00:23:17.875 --> 00:23:19.125
[Lidia laughs uncomfortably]

439
00:23:19.208 --> 00:23:22.291
<i>La traviata </i>is playing tomorrow
at the Regio. and she'll be Violetta.

440
00:23:22.375 --> 00:23:24.333
That's why we took the liberty
to come unannounced.

441
00:23:24.416 --> 00:23:25.750
That is quite all right.

442
00:23:26.500 --> 00:23:29.541
And Consuelo.
Jacopo must consider himself very lucky.

443
00:23:29.625 --> 00:23:30.666
[Consuelo] Hm. I know.

444
00:23:30.750 --> 00:23:33.083
[Consuelo and Teresa tittering]

445
00:23:33.166 --> 00:23:36.041
Forgive me.
I just got back. and I have to…

446
00:23:38.500 --> 00:23:40.500
go to my room. I'll see you later.

447
00:23:40.583 --> 00:23:42.250
[Teresa] I hope you'll stay for dinner.

448
00:23:42.333 --> 00:23:44.500
- [Consuelo] Oh. yes!
- [Jacopo] No. no. no.

449
00:23:46.666 --> 00:23:49.416
But we could at least spend
Easter together. right?

450
00:23:49.500 --> 00:23:51.916
Teresa. Easter's a long way off.
We'll think about it later.

451
00:24:12.416 --> 00:24:14.416
[uneasy music playing]

452
00:24:15.458 --> 00:24:17.583
[coroner] Death was immediate.

453
00:24:17.666 --> 00:24:20.041
Fracture of the occipital plate.

454
00:24:20.666 --> 00:24:22.583
As you can see. though.

455
00:24:22.666 --> 00:24:25.458
there are some bruises here.

456
00:24:25.541 --> 00:24:27.791
They're from a series of injections.

457
00:24:28.625 --> 00:24:33.208
Would you be able to tell us if the victim
had actually taken any sleeping agents?

458
00:24:33.291 --> 00:24:34.833
[coroner] Well. it's hard to say.

459
00:24:34.916 --> 00:24:37.708
but the syringe we found
contained some traces.

460
00:24:37.791 --> 00:24:39.666
Excuse me. What is this?

461
00:24:40.458 --> 00:24:42.708
This is a fairly recent wound.

462
00:24:42.791 --> 00:24:44.333
Ten days. maybe.

463
00:24:44.416 --> 00:24:48.000
But it's very superficial.
It can't have caused the fall.

464
00:24:48.083 --> 00:24:51.041
[mysterious music playing]

465
00:24:52.541 --> 00:24:53.833
[Enrico] <i>What are you thinking?</i>

466
00:24:54.416 --> 00:24:57.000
Did you ever make a blood oath
when you were a child?

467
00:24:57.083 --> 00:24:58.458
[Enrico] No.

468
00:24:58.541 --> 00:25:02.000
Well. you swear to be friends forever
and to always tell each other the truth.

469
00:25:02.083 --> 00:25:04.958
- I had normal friends. Lidia.
- No. you didn't have any friends. Enrico.

470
00:25:05.041 --> 00:25:06.166
I'm sorry.

471
00:25:06.958 --> 00:25:10.000
- Giorgio was my friend.
- He was the gardener. He was 55.

472
00:25:10.083 --> 00:25:11.750
We don't have to go over this again.

473
00:25:11.833 --> 00:25:14.666
[camel grunting. snorting]

474
00:25:16.041 --> 00:25:16.958
[Lidia] Mm.

475
00:25:19.583 --> 00:25:20.583
Mm.

476
00:25:23.583 --> 00:25:27.041
[suspenseful music playing]

477
00:25:28.125 --> 00:25:29.166
What's your name?

478
00:25:30.500 --> 00:25:31.875
Susanna.

479
00:25:33.416 --> 00:25:35.000
<i>I'm sorry. I really can't.</i>

480
00:25:35.083 --> 00:25:38.583
I swore to Miranda that I wouldn't
talk to anyone about her stuff.

481
00:25:38.666 --> 00:25:41.125
[Enrico] Susanna. a person is in prison.

482
00:25:41.208 --> 00:25:43.875
and it is your duty
to help us set the record straight.

483
00:25:43.958 --> 00:25:46.125
No. we certainly were not
having an affair.

484
00:25:46.208 --> 00:25:48.625
I don't know why
Susanna told you something like that.

485
00:25:48.708 --> 00:25:52.750
The prosecutor is convinced
that this is your wife's motive.

486
00:25:54.000 --> 00:25:57.250
So. if something happened.
anything you can think of.

487
00:25:58.125 --> 00:25:59.791
then we need to know.

488
00:25:59.875 --> 00:26:02.916
[intriguing string music playing]

489
00:26:03.666 --> 00:26:04.958
[Lidia] <i>I understand. you know?</i>

490
00:26:05.916 --> 00:26:08.916
I know how important
an oath to a friend is.

491
00:26:11.291 --> 00:26:13.375
We just want to rule out the possibility

492
00:26:13.458 --> 00:26:18.083
that Miranda and Rubino
were not having a romantic relationship.

493
00:26:21.166 --> 00:26:22.875
We can't rule it out?

494
00:26:24.375 --> 00:26:27.291
I don't know.
maybe Miranda made it up. right?

495
00:26:27.875 --> 00:26:30.708
I cared about her. I really did.

496
00:26:30.791 --> 00:26:34.250
But she was a girl that made things up.
and she was always full of secrets.

497
00:26:34.333 --> 00:26:35.666
She was strange.

498
00:26:35.750 --> 00:26:36.750
Strange how?

499
00:26:39.625 --> 00:26:41.000
Last week when I saw her.

500
00:26:41.083 --> 00:26:44.416
she was sitting in front
of that big fancy hotel. the Regio.

501
00:26:44.500 --> 00:26:45.541
I tried to avoid her.

502
00:26:45.625 --> 00:26:48.666
I didn't want her to get the impression
that I was following her or anything.

503
00:26:48.750 --> 00:26:49.958
But it was strange.

504
00:26:50.041 --> 00:26:51.750
Yes. but why?

505
00:26:51.833 --> 00:26:55.208
Because. well. it looked like
she was waiting for someone.

506
00:26:56.500 --> 00:26:58.500
[Enrico] <i>Honestly.</i>
<i>I don't trust either of them.</i>

507
00:26:58.583 --> 00:27:00.291
But it's not a matter of trust. Enrico.

508
00:27:00.375 --> 00:27:04.125
We just have to go to the Regio
and ask if anyone saw Miranda.

509
00:27:04.208 --> 00:27:05.208
Even if they saw her.

510
00:27:05.291 --> 00:27:07.291
what does that have to do
with Lorena being jealous?

511
00:27:07.375 --> 00:27:09.541
It has nothing to do with it.
but if Miranda went there

512
00:27:09.625 --> 00:27:10.875
and didn't tell her best friend.

513
00:27:10.958 --> 00:27:12.791
it means there was something
she was ashamed of.

514
00:27:12.875 --> 00:27:14.833
or that could get her into trouble.

515
00:27:18.458 --> 00:27:20.833
- What's going on?
- [Lidia] Go. I'll be right there.

516
00:27:20.916 --> 00:27:22.916
[sombre music playing]

517
00:27:27.916 --> 00:27:29.333
I can explain.

518
00:27:33.666 --> 00:27:37.708
- It seems a lifetime.
- [Lidia] Mm. I noticed.

519
00:27:39.250 --> 00:27:40.250
[Grazia] I'm sorry. Lidia.

520
00:27:40.333 --> 00:27:43.000
I just want to understand
why you didn't wait for me to get back.

521
00:27:43.083 --> 00:27:45.125
- [Grazia] I'm sorry. I couldn't wait.
- Why not?

522
00:27:46.791 --> 00:27:48.916
There's no debt. I lied to you.

523
00:27:50.000 --> 00:27:52.416
I was trying to run away from my husband.

524
00:27:53.166 --> 00:27:55.166
I'd found someone
who would get me across the border.

525
00:27:55.250 --> 00:27:58.375
but when I tried to give him the necklace.
he wouldn't accept it.

526
00:28:01.875 --> 00:28:04.791
Why didn't you just say so? Why?

527
00:28:06.291 --> 00:28:08.000
Because I was ashamed.

528
00:28:11.000 --> 00:28:12.875
Grazia. you don't have to be ashamed.

529
00:28:13.625 --> 00:28:15.208
Huh? It's me.

530
00:28:17.291 --> 00:28:19.125
[voice breaking] I abhor him. Lidia.

531
00:28:21.958 --> 00:28:24.375
He's controlling.
He tells me what to wear.

532
00:28:25.375 --> 00:28:27.125
He doesn't let me see anyone.

533
00:28:29.750 --> 00:28:33.333
One time. I told him he'd been too harsh
with how he dealt with Mila…

534
00:28:33.416 --> 00:28:35.625
He beat me within an inch of my life.

535
00:28:37.166 --> 00:28:40.583
And then he kept me at home for a month.
telling everyone I was sick.

536
00:28:43.625 --> 00:28:46.916
- I cannot go back home to that.
- No. Of course not.

537
00:28:52.000 --> 00:28:54.000
Have you thought about separating?

538
00:28:54.083 --> 00:28:56.333
- [scoffs] Is that a thing?
- It is.

539
00:28:57.041 --> 00:28:58.791
Of course. you both need to agree.

540
00:28:58.875 --> 00:29:02.541
- That's not something he'd agree to.
- Well. then. we'll take him to court.

541
00:29:02.625 --> 00:29:04.625
[Grazia sighs heavily]

542
00:29:07.791 --> 00:29:09.250
No more tears.

543
00:29:09.333 --> 00:29:10.333
No.

544
00:29:11.208 --> 00:29:12.250
Listen here.

545
00:29:13.791 --> 00:29:17.750
[inhales] Just think about me. Mm?

546
00:29:18.458 --> 00:29:19.875
About the two of us.

547
00:29:20.625 --> 00:29:25.416
About the time when we lived together
in that awful house. [laughs]

548
00:29:25.500 --> 00:29:27.083
Completely broke.

549
00:29:28.500 --> 00:29:31.875
And how we stole coal
in order to keep ourselves warm.

550
00:29:31.958 --> 00:29:32.958
[Grazia sniffles]

551
00:29:34.083 --> 00:29:36.125
We're still here. aren't we?

552
00:29:40.750 --> 00:29:44.041
- And I think we deserve a strong drink.
- [Grazia chuckles softly]

553
00:29:45.416 --> 00:29:47.625
- Very strong drink.
- [Lidia laughs]

554
00:29:49.791 --> 00:29:52.250
Come… Come on.

555
00:29:52.333 --> 00:29:53.208
[Grazia chuckles]

556
00:29:53.291 --> 00:29:54.875
[hopeful music playing]

557
00:29:58.541 --> 00:29:59.833
[Lidia] So…

558
00:30:01.250 --> 00:30:02.458
pick one.

559
00:30:02.541 --> 00:30:05.833
- [Grazia] I have to change my clothes?
- To drink where we're going. yes.

560
00:30:06.416 --> 00:30:08.666
I'll be wearing a dress of Lidia Poët?

561
00:30:08.750 --> 00:30:10.041
[both laughing]

562
00:30:14.083 --> 00:30:15.250
[bell dings]

563
00:30:15.333 --> 00:30:18.666
So. indulge me for five minutes.
then we'll go to the bar.

564
00:30:18.750 --> 00:30:21.375
- That'll make them think you're a floozie.
- Yes. that's the idea.

565
00:30:21.458 --> 00:30:24.250
You see.
everyone likes a floozie. you know?

566
00:30:24.333 --> 00:30:25.958
- No…
- Yes. indeed. really…

567
00:30:26.041 --> 00:30:28.500
I'm sorry. but you can't stay here.

568
00:30:28.583 --> 00:30:31.375
- We just wanted to have a quiet drink.
- No.

569
00:30:31.458 --> 00:30:33.666
[humorous string music playing]

570
00:30:33.750 --> 00:30:39.458
Well. right. um. may I at least ask
if you've ever seen this lady?

571
00:30:42.708 --> 00:30:44.458
She asked you a question.
What is the matter?

572
00:30:44.541 --> 00:30:46.541
- The matter's your profession.
- Ah.

573
00:30:46.625 --> 00:30:48.458
Well. apparently.
not everyone likes floozies.

574
00:30:48.541 --> 00:30:51.000
Look. my friend here
is the Electorate Poët's sister.

575
00:30:51.083 --> 00:30:53.625
- She's all over the newspapers.
- Lidia Poët.

576
00:30:53.708 --> 00:30:56.333
Yes. and I'm Prince Vittorio Emanuele.
and I'm in…

577
00:30:56.416 --> 00:30:59.250
Obviously. you don't read any newspapers.
It's the truth.

578
00:30:59.333 --> 00:31:01.041
- Security!
- Oh. wait…

579
00:31:01.125 --> 00:31:02.625
- Security?
- No need to call security.

580
00:31:02.708 --> 00:31:04.416
I can't believe it! Lidia Poët!

581
00:31:04.500 --> 00:31:07.125
Join our friends. We are all at the bar
with the rest of them.

582
00:31:07.208 --> 00:31:10.333
- They're with me. thank you.
- It was an honour. Your Highness.

583
00:31:10.416 --> 00:31:11.833
If you don't mind…

584
00:31:11.916 --> 00:31:15.375
Gentlemen. as destiny would have it.
look who I found… Lidia Poët!

585
00:31:15.458 --> 00:31:17.416
- [people applauding]
- Ah.

586
00:31:18.625 --> 00:31:20.666
- Interesting.
- Bonjour.

587
00:31:21.583 --> 00:31:23.250
[Lidia] Thank you.

588
00:31:27.458 --> 00:31:28.708
<i>Putain. putain. putain!</i>

589
00:31:29.291 --> 00:31:31.541
Looks like Jacopo
and the prosecutor are here.

590
00:31:31.625 --> 00:31:34.291
- Ah. I'll get you a drink.
- Thank you.

591
00:31:40.000 --> 00:31:41.000
Jacopo.

592
00:31:41.083 --> 00:31:42.000
Lidia.

593
00:31:42.583 --> 00:31:44.458
- Prosecutor.
- Ms Poët.

594
00:31:45.583 --> 00:31:47.708
Ladies and gentlemen. please be quiet!

595
00:31:47.791 --> 00:31:50.750
- [man shushing] Quiet. Quiet.
- [Consuelo] Señores. let's play a game.

596
00:31:50.833 --> 00:31:52.666
A fun little drinking game.

597
00:31:52.750 --> 00:31:54.750
[all cheering and applauding]

598
00:31:56.083 --> 00:31:58.333
- Jacopo. explain the rules. please.
- Ah. yes. yes. yes.

599
00:31:58.416 --> 00:32:00.541
Uh. help me if I forget something.

600
00:32:00.625 --> 00:32:02.375
The basic rules are. uh.

601
00:32:02.458 --> 00:32:05.750
the person taking their turn
must reveal an experience

602
00:32:05.833 --> 00:32:07.875
that they have never had before. right?

603
00:32:07.958 --> 00:32:10.125
- To the room.
- [Jacopo] To the room. yes. out loud.

604
00:32:10.208 --> 00:32:14.750
And if any of the other players
have indeed experienced it.

605
00:32:14.833 --> 00:32:17.333
they must drink a glass of cognac!

606
00:32:17.416 --> 00:32:20.833
[all laughing and applauding]

607
00:32:20.916 --> 00:32:22.375
Can we lie?

608
00:32:23.125 --> 00:32:26.166
Well. it's not the point of the game.
but. eh… Who are we to judge. hey?

609
00:32:26.250 --> 00:32:27.333
[all laugh]

610
00:32:27.416 --> 00:32:28.416
[Consuelo] It's my turn!

611
00:32:29.375 --> 00:32:31.041
- The glass. Okay.
- Thank you.

612
00:32:31.750 --> 00:32:33.916
[Consuelo] So. never have I…

613
00:32:34.833 --> 00:32:37.416
fallen in love before.

614
00:32:37.500 --> 00:32:38.625
[all tittering]

615
00:32:38.708 --> 00:32:41.083
Consuelo… this is how you tell me?

616
00:32:41.166 --> 00:32:43.541
[Consuelo] I'm only with you
because you're handsome. my love.

617
00:32:43.625 --> 00:32:46.083
[all laughing]

618
00:32:49.333 --> 00:32:53.791
Uh. madam. you're married.
but you don't drink. hm?

619
00:32:53.875 --> 00:32:55.500
Poor husband. [chuckles]

620
00:32:55.583 --> 00:32:56.708
[chuckles softly]

621
00:32:56.791 --> 00:32:59.083
Never met a woman
who cited love as a reason to marry.

622
00:32:59.166 --> 00:33:01.416
My sister! My sister.

623
00:33:01.500 --> 00:33:04.333
Who. by the way.
is an incredible character. [laughing]

624
00:33:04.416 --> 00:33:05.916
Your turn. Grazia.

625
00:33:06.000 --> 00:33:07.000
[Grazia] My turn?

626
00:33:09.416 --> 00:33:10.833
Never have I…

627
00:33:12.708 --> 00:33:13.708
been made to wear a corset

628
00:33:13.791 --> 00:33:16.916
as tight as the one
Lidia squeezed me into this evening.

629
00:33:17.000 --> 00:33:18.041
[all laughing]

630
00:33:19.375 --> 00:33:21.625
You no shame? You just want to get drunk?

631
00:33:21.708 --> 00:33:25.166
What do you know about
what I did in Paris. my sweet love?

632
00:33:25.250 --> 00:33:27.708
- My turn.
- [Consuelo] Yes. go on.

633
00:33:29.416 --> 00:33:31.416
[pensive music playing]

634
00:33:31.500 --> 00:33:32.666
Well. then…

635
00:33:34.000 --> 00:33:35.583
Never have I…

636
00:33:39.125 --> 00:33:42.166
had the pleasure
of meeting a trapeze artist.

637
00:33:42.875 --> 00:33:45.666
[compelling choral music playing]

638
00:33:45.750 --> 00:33:46.958
[people murmuring]

639
00:33:47.541 --> 00:33:50.958
But I have. More than one. actually.

640
00:33:51.041 --> 00:33:53.500
Mr Calvart
is a great French circus impresario.

641
00:33:54.083 --> 00:33:57.333
After this glass. I definitely
won't be able to stand up any more.

642
00:33:57.416 --> 00:33:59.833
[all laughing]

643
00:33:59.916 --> 00:34:03.000
{\an8}- [man] A toast to the impresario!
- May I have a word in private with you?

644
00:34:03.708 --> 00:34:05.750
Yes. with pleasure. yes.

645
00:34:05.833 --> 00:34:09.083
[pensive music playing]

646
00:34:09.166 --> 00:34:11.125
She wanted to join my company.

647
00:34:13.083 --> 00:34:15.708
Her family circus wasn't enough for her.

648
00:34:15.791 --> 00:34:21.250
She wanted… a bigger audience.
to travel the world and… [chuckles]

649
00:34:21.333 --> 00:34:23.250
…become famous.

650
00:34:23.333 --> 00:34:26.791
So I promised I'd come
and see her at the Sunday show.

651
00:34:28.125 --> 00:34:30.500
The one where she had the accident.

652
00:34:30.583 --> 00:34:32.583
[Calvart] Yes. That one.

653
00:34:33.375 --> 00:34:35.166
But I couldn't make it.

654
00:34:36.000 --> 00:34:38.875
I found out about the accident
from the newspaper.

655
00:34:41.791 --> 00:34:43.416
I'm sorry. madam.

656
00:34:43.500 --> 00:34:45.791
I'm afraid that's all the help
I can give you.

657
00:34:45.875 --> 00:34:48.458
That's all right.
You've helped so much already.

658
00:34:48.541 --> 00:34:50.375
<i>- Merci.</i>
<i>- Je vous en prie.</i>

659
00:35:05.708 --> 00:35:07.708
[pensive music fades]

660
00:35:12.166 --> 00:35:13.416
Ms Poët.

661
00:35:15.833 --> 00:35:17.208
I'm happy to see you here.

662
00:35:17.291 --> 00:35:18.458
Me too.

663
00:35:19.208 --> 00:35:21.083
And I have a surprise for you.

664
00:35:22.583 --> 00:35:25.875
I was thinking. if being seen together
in Turin is a problem.

665
00:35:26.583 --> 00:35:27.416
and it is…

666
00:35:27.500 --> 00:35:28.333
Mm-hmm.

667
00:35:28.875 --> 00:35:30.583
…we could go somewhere else.

668
00:35:31.125 --> 00:35:32.291
[Lidia laughs softly]

669
00:35:35.000 --> 00:35:36.625
TURIN CENTRAL STATION - VIENNA

670
00:35:37.500 --> 00:35:38.541
Vienna.

671
00:35:38.625 --> 00:35:40.333
[Fourneau] I got them this morning. yes.

672
00:35:40.416 --> 00:35:44.000
Imagine. five days. you and me.

673
00:35:44.083 --> 00:35:45.875
in a place where nobody knows.

674
00:35:45.958 --> 00:35:47.458
Ooh…

675
00:35:49.625 --> 00:35:51.000
[Fourneau] What do you say?

676
00:35:53.166 --> 00:35:54.916
That sounds wonderful.

677
00:35:55.000 --> 00:35:56.708
- [Fourneau chuckles]
- Very well.

678
00:35:58.833 --> 00:36:03.041
Just enough time to sort out
the situation with Grazia.

679
00:36:04.250 --> 00:36:05.291
Yes.

680
00:36:05.375 --> 00:36:07.208
[Fourneau] Did you find
the money to help her?

681
00:36:07.291 --> 00:36:08.416
No.

682
00:36:08.500 --> 00:36:12.458
Luckily. I'd say. because she needed it
to run away from her husband and…

683
00:36:12.541 --> 00:36:15.250
[inhales] …to disappear permanently.

684
00:36:15.333 --> 00:36:18.291
I'm suggesting legal separation
to see if that may help.

685
00:36:18.375 --> 00:36:20.833
[Grazia laughing. chatting]

686
00:36:20.916 --> 00:36:22.375
[Fourneau] What did he do to her?

687
00:36:24.458 --> 00:36:25.666
He beat her.

688
00:36:26.791 --> 00:36:27.791
And…

689
00:36:29.083 --> 00:36:32.708
she told me that
he almost killed her once.

690
00:36:32.791 --> 00:36:34.791
[sombre music playing]

691
00:36:36.916 --> 00:36:40.083
It's just that in court.
what she says won't be enough.

692
00:36:40.166 --> 00:36:42.208
[man. Grazia speaking indistinctly]

693
00:36:42.291 --> 00:36:43.208
[Grazia laughing]

694
00:36:43.291 --> 00:36:44.583
I know.

695
00:36:45.375 --> 00:36:47.583
- [Grazia laughs. yelps]
- Careful. careful.

696
00:36:47.666 --> 00:36:49.833
So… so sorry. [laughing]

697
00:36:49.916 --> 00:36:51.625
- [Grazia retching]
- Good. that's it.

698
00:36:51.708 --> 00:36:55.958
- Well done. well done. That's it.
- [Grazia moaning. coughing]

699
00:36:56.041 --> 00:36:58.000
- [groans]
- [both laughing]

700
00:36:58.083 --> 00:37:00.208
I told you I didn't have
the stamina for it these days.

701
00:37:00.291 --> 00:37:05.250
- Yes. I can see that.
- [Grazia laughing] Oh…

702
00:37:07.125 --> 00:37:08.541
I'm so sorry.

703
00:37:09.541 --> 00:37:12.166
- Don't you worry.
- No. really. I'm sorry.

704
00:37:15.500 --> 00:37:17.666
I nearly did something disastrous.

705
00:37:17.750 --> 00:37:18.833
[exhales heavily]

706
00:37:20.166 --> 00:37:22.708
And running away is an act of desperation.

707
00:37:22.791 --> 00:37:25.125
[sombre music playing]

708
00:37:25.208 --> 00:37:27.250
I can't run away my whole life.

709
00:37:28.958 --> 00:37:31.000
It wouldn't be fair to Mila.

710
00:37:33.583 --> 00:37:34.958
Nor to myself.

711
00:37:53.916 --> 00:37:55.375
Let's get out of here.

712
00:37:58.875 --> 00:37:59.916
Sure.

713
00:38:02.916 --> 00:38:04.208
Those feathers!

714
00:38:04.291 --> 00:38:07.875
[both laughing]

715
00:38:09.291 --> 00:38:10.583
[Enrico] "Article 150".

716
00:38:10.666 --> 00:38:15.083
"Separation may be requested
on the grounds of excesses. abuse.

717
00:38:16.833 --> 00:38:19.208
threats. and serious affronts".

718
00:38:20.458 --> 00:38:21.458
[book closes]

719
00:38:21.541 --> 00:38:23.041
Let us be clear.

720
00:38:23.125 --> 00:38:26.125
Domestic violence
is not a crime in our legal system.

721
00:38:26.208 --> 00:38:30.916
and I strongly doubt that a court
would rely on your word alone.

722
00:38:31.666 --> 00:38:35.083
In my opinion.
it would be better to follow Article 158.

723
00:38:35.166 --> 00:38:36.791
"Consensual separation".

724
00:38:36.875 --> 00:38:39.083
- [Lidia] Yes.
- [Grazia] Would my daughter stay with me?

725
00:38:39.166 --> 00:38:42.375
Um… If your husband agrees. then yes.

726
00:38:42.458 --> 00:38:43.583
That's not something he'd do.

727
00:38:44.333 --> 00:38:49.041
And. if possible. at this time.
try to maintain good relations.

728
00:38:49.125 --> 00:38:50.750
We'll try to have a word with him.

729
00:38:50.833 --> 00:38:53.250
We'll make him understand
it's in his best interest to give in.

730
00:38:53.333 --> 00:38:55.458
because we're in a position
to take him to court.

731
00:38:56.041 --> 00:38:59.083
- But I don't want to go back there.
- [Lidia] In fact. you're staying here.

732
00:39:00.416 --> 00:39:01.958
For as long as you want to.

733
00:39:02.500 --> 00:39:03.916
[laughs softly] Right?

734
00:39:04.000 --> 00:39:05.333
Certainly.

735
00:39:05.416 --> 00:39:08.000
I don't know how to thank you.
You've been so kind.

736
00:39:09.125 --> 00:39:09.958
Seriously.

737
00:39:10.541 --> 00:39:11.583
Thank you.

738
00:39:12.833 --> 00:39:15.916
Now I'll go and see if Mila
is up to more mischief. [chuckles]

739
00:39:23.708 --> 00:39:25.500
[Enrico sighs]

740
00:39:25.583 --> 00:39:26.916
Let's go.

741
00:39:27.000 --> 00:39:28.916
- Put your jacket on.
- Why?

742
00:39:29.000 --> 00:39:31.625
Miranda wanted to run away
from her family.

743
00:39:32.291 --> 00:39:34.958
She wanted to join Calvart's circus.

744
00:39:35.041 --> 00:39:38.750
That's why she wanted to perform
at any cost that night.

745
00:39:39.958 --> 00:39:43.125
Because it was the only chance
she had to convince him.

746
00:39:43.208 --> 00:39:45.208
[Enrico] And maybe someone
wanted to stop her.

747
00:39:46.000 --> 00:39:47.541
Do you know who that might be?

748
00:39:49.416 --> 00:39:51.791
I can only think of Paride.

749
00:39:51.875 --> 00:39:55.000
He's Miranda's grandfather.
He would never allow her to leave.

750
00:39:55.083 --> 00:39:56.000
Of course.

751
00:39:56.083 --> 00:39:57.708
There's no way he would've switched vials.

752
00:39:57.791 --> 00:39:58.791
No. indeed.

753
00:39:58.875 --> 00:40:01.541
And yet… Well. why not? It adds up.

754
00:40:01.625 --> 00:40:03.333
Because it doesn't add up. Enrico.

755
00:40:03.416 --> 00:40:06.500
If Paride had known that his granddaughter
had taken a sedative.

756
00:40:06.583 --> 00:40:09.791
he would never have let her
get on the trapeze like that. No!

757
00:40:10.916 --> 00:40:12.166
- No.
- [Lidia] No. exactly.

758
00:40:12.833 --> 00:40:15.666
If he wanted to.
he could have cancelled Miranda's act.

759
00:40:15.750 --> 00:40:17.041
He didn't need to sabotage it.

760
00:40:17.125 --> 00:40:20.041
No. it must have been someone
with less power.

761
00:40:20.125 --> 00:40:23.500
less authority. and who couldn't
bear the thought of living without her.

762
00:40:24.791 --> 00:40:27.041
It was someone who knew.

763
00:40:27.125 --> 00:40:29.750
but couldn't say a word to anyone.

764
00:40:30.458 --> 00:40:33.250
<i>Because they had taken a blood oath.</i>

765
00:40:33.333 --> 00:40:35.125
[Paride yelling] Susanna!

766
00:40:38.958 --> 00:40:40.291
Susanna!

767
00:40:40.375 --> 00:40:41.916
[suspenseful music playing]

768
00:40:50.083 --> 00:40:51.375
Enrico!

769
00:41:18.541 --> 00:41:19.791
[music stops abruptly]

770
00:41:19.875 --> 00:41:21.750
- Susanna!
- Go away!

771
00:41:22.833 --> 00:41:25.083
- Susanna. come down.
- If you come up. I'll jump.

772
00:41:25.166 --> 00:41:27.000
- I'll stay here.
- [Susanna] I'll jump!

773
00:41:27.083 --> 00:41:28.458
I'm staying down here.

774
00:41:29.208 --> 00:41:30.916
- Susanna!
- Wait. wait. wait…

775
00:41:31.000 --> 00:41:34.625
- [Susanna] I'll jump. I don't care!
- No one's coming up! No one's coming up.

776
00:41:35.791 --> 00:41:40.666
[panting] Susanna. I know…
that you didn't want to kill Miranda.

777
00:41:40.750 --> 00:41:42.000
You don't know anything!

778
00:41:42.083 --> 00:41:43.416
Trust me. I know.

779
00:41:45.708 --> 00:41:48.000
I understand what you're going through.

780
00:41:48.083 --> 00:41:50.083
I made a pact in blood
with my best friend.

781
00:41:52.250 --> 00:41:54.041
No secrets. right?

782
00:41:56.000 --> 00:42:00.083
And then she got pregnant.
she got married.

783
00:42:00.166 --> 00:42:03.416
and to this day. I still regret
all the thoughts that I had.

784
00:42:04.041 --> 00:42:07.583
Because I didn't want her to get married.
I didn't want her to become a mother.

785
00:42:07.666 --> 00:42:09.875
That way. I wouldn't have been left alone.

786
00:42:12.041 --> 00:42:15.416
You didn't know Miranda wanted
to perform without a safety net.

787
00:42:17.000 --> 00:42:19.416
You just didn't want Calvart to see her.

788
00:42:21.583 --> 00:42:24.625
Because you were afraid
of losing her. right?

789
00:42:27.041 --> 00:42:29.833
["Safe with Me" by Soap&Skin playing]

790
00:42:35.041 --> 00:42:37.083
[breathes deeply]

791
00:42:41.166 --> 00:42:43.916
[Lidia] <i>Most of the time.</i>
<i>people kill out of hatred.</i>

792
00:42:44.000 --> 00:42:47.000
<i>but in the case of</i>
<i>the young trapeze artist Miranda Laforêt.</i>

793
00:42:47.083 --> 00:42:49.083
<i>there is only one truth.</i>

794
00:42:49.166 --> 00:42:51.041
<i>No one wanted to kill.</i>

795
00:42:51.125 --> 00:42:53.541
<i>A mistake was made. yes.</i>

796
00:42:55.791 --> 00:42:57.333
<i>But at the root of the mistake</i>

797
00:42:57.416 --> 00:43:00.541
<i>was the noblest feeling</i>
<i>that human beings are capable of.</i>

798
00:43:01.500 --> 00:43:02.666
<i>Friendship.</i>

799
00:43:02.750 --> 00:43:03.916
[all cheering]

800
00:43:04.000 --> 00:43:06.458
<i>♪ It's hard to find it ♪</i>

801
00:43:07.291 --> 00:43:08.791
<i>♪ When you're into it ♪</i>

802
00:43:08.875 --> 00:43:10.875
[Lidia] <i>And true friendship lasts forever.</i>

803
00:43:10.958 --> 00:43:13.625
<i>♪ The sun. replace it… ♪</i>

804
00:43:13.708 --> 00:43:16.041
[Lidia] <i>But sometimes.</i>
<i>friendship is so intense</i>

805
00:43:16.125 --> 00:43:17.833
<i>that it becomes dangerous.</i>

806
00:43:17.916 --> 00:43:19.500
<i>and the fear of losing a friend</i>

807
00:43:19.583 --> 00:43:22.625
<i>can push</i>
<i>the most delicate and sensitive person</i>

808
00:43:22.708 --> 00:43:25.166
<i>to display horrible selfishness.</i>

809
00:43:25.791 --> 00:43:28.833
<i>Susanna Garenne did not want to kill.</i>

810
00:43:28.916 --> 00:43:30.416
<i>On the contrary.</i>

811
00:43:30.500 --> 00:43:33.541
<i>she would have wanted her friend</i>
<i>to live with her forever.</i>

812
00:43:35.500 --> 00:43:38.500
<i>♪ No love can be… ♪</i>

813
00:43:38.583 --> 00:43:41.916
[Lidia] <i>That was her goal. Not death.</i>

814
00:43:43.208 --> 00:43:45.958
<i>♪ No love can be ♪</i>

815
00:43:47.166 --> 00:43:49.333
<i>♪ Safe with me… ♪</i>

816
00:43:50.250 --> 00:43:51.666
[Lidia] <i>And therefore.</i>

817
00:43:53.333 --> 00:43:55.041
<i>the charge of voluntary homicide</i>

818
00:43:55.125 --> 00:43:59.583
<i>is absolutely unjust</i>
<i>and does not correspond to the real facts.</i>

819
00:44:05.583 --> 00:44:08.875
Spending Easter with my family.
isn't that… mmm…

820
00:44:09.708 --> 00:44:11.166
a bit too much?

821
00:44:12.083 --> 00:44:14.083
Why not just the two of us?

822
00:44:14.750 --> 00:44:19.708
We could arrange to have brought up
some roasted lamb. champagne…

823
00:44:20.333 --> 00:44:21.416
[Consuelo] My love.

824
00:44:22.625 --> 00:44:25.583
if there is a problem with Lidia.
you can just tell me.

825
00:44:27.541 --> 00:44:30.291
Do you think…
she's still burning with love?

826
00:44:30.375 --> 00:44:34.541
No. "burning with love"
is an exaggeration. um… [inhales]

827
00:44:36.833 --> 00:44:38.625
You decide. Jacopo.

828
00:44:39.416 --> 00:44:42.083
I don't want her to suffer because of me.

829
00:44:42.166 --> 00:44:44.125
But it's been six months.

830
00:44:44.208 --> 00:44:47.958
Maybe it's time to. you know…
make peace and move on. right?

831
00:44:48.041 --> 00:44:49.375
[Jacopo laughs]

832
00:44:49.458 --> 00:44:52.083
Come on. don't laugh.
I know I sound funny.

833
00:44:52.166 --> 00:44:53.750
- No! No. no. no.
- [Consuelo] What?

834
00:44:53.833 --> 00:44:56.750
My love. what you're saying isn't funny.
it's old-fashioned.

835
00:44:56.833 --> 00:44:59.166
Your words are suave.

836
00:44:59.250 --> 00:45:02.333
- [Consuelo] Mm?
- My love. it's pure poetry.

837
00:45:03.166 --> 00:45:04.416
Yes.

838
00:45:04.500 --> 00:45:05.708
Come here.

839
00:45:05.791 --> 00:45:09.666
- [Consuelo giggling]
- Come sit right here.

840
00:45:09.750 --> 00:45:13.500
[Consuelo singing "La traviata"
in Italian]

841
00:45:20.333 --> 00:45:21.375
She's brilliant.

842
00:45:22.125 --> 00:45:23.833
And very. very nice.

843
00:45:23.916 --> 00:45:25.125
- And beautiful.
- [Lidia] Yes.

844
00:45:25.208 --> 00:45:27.708
[continues singing "La traviata"]

845
00:45:27.791 --> 00:45:29.541
But she still doesn't know me well enough.

846
00:45:30.708 --> 00:45:33.958
Sooner or later. she'll realise
she's made a mistake. Right?

847
00:45:34.041 --> 00:45:35.250
- Yes. afraid so.
- Yes.

848
00:45:35.333 --> 00:45:36.458
- Yes.
- Yes.

849
00:45:36.541 --> 00:45:37.541
[both laugh]

850
00:45:38.666 --> 00:45:42.500
And what about you and your prosecutor?

851
00:45:42.583 --> 00:45:45.750
[scoffs] What prosecutor?

852
00:45:50.333 --> 00:45:51.666
It's good.

853
00:45:52.583 --> 00:45:53.750
I'm very happy.

854
00:45:54.541 --> 00:45:55.583
Splendid.

855
00:45:57.416 --> 00:45:58.416
I am too.

856
00:45:58.500 --> 00:45:59.500
Good.

857
00:46:11.875 --> 00:46:14.833
The angels in heaven could not match
the pure harmony of your voice.

858
00:46:14.916 --> 00:46:15.791
Thank you.

859
00:46:15.875 --> 00:46:18.041
- [Enrico and Jacopo] Cheers!
- [Teresa] Congratulations.

860
00:46:19.333 --> 00:46:21.958
Jacopo told me
that your daughter likes music too.

861
00:46:22.041 --> 00:46:23.541
- Oh yes.
- I'd like to meet her some day.

862
00:46:23.625 --> 00:46:25.916
[chuckles awkwardly]
Unfortunately. she gave up.

863
00:46:26.000 --> 00:46:28.291
Now she attends
the École Supérieure in Paris.

864
00:46:28.375 --> 00:46:31.458
[gasps] Oh. how wonderful!
Paris is amazing in the springtime.

865
00:46:31.541 --> 00:46:34.583
Maybe. but she could have found
a week for her family.

866
00:46:34.666 --> 00:46:37.708
I know young people don't care
much about traditions. but…

867
00:46:37.791 --> 00:46:42.833
Easter has a spiritual meaning that is…
<i>muy profundo. </i>[chuckles]

868
00:46:42.916 --> 00:46:45.333
[Lidia] He's a polyglot.
Spanish. French. I mean. he's…

869
00:46:45.416 --> 00:46:46.791
[Albertina] Excuse me!

870
00:46:46.875 --> 00:46:48.958
- Yes?
- There's someone asking for you.

871
00:46:49.041 --> 00:46:52.375
Honestly. this is quite inappropriate.
We just sat down at the table.

872
00:46:52.458 --> 00:46:53.541
[man] You're right. ma'am.

873
00:46:53.625 --> 00:46:55.750
- In fact. I apologise to everyone.
- Daddy!

874
00:46:55.833 --> 00:46:57.458
[man] Hi. princess.

875
00:46:57.541 --> 00:46:59.166
Do you know how much
I missed you. darling?

876
00:47:00.125 --> 00:47:04.208
I would not have been this inappropriate
if this was not a matter of urgency.

877
00:47:04.291 --> 00:47:06.541
[uneasy music playing]

878
00:47:06.625 --> 00:47:07.958
Please. Captain.

879
00:47:08.041 --> 00:47:10.291
if you would like to join
our frugal lunch.

880
00:47:10.375 --> 00:47:12.166
- [Lidia] Mm-mm.
- [man] No. don't bother. sir.

881
00:47:12.250 --> 00:47:15.750
If I may. I'd like to speak
to my wife for a minute. In private.

882
00:47:15.833 --> 00:47:17.458
No. if you have something to say. say it…

883
00:47:17.541 --> 00:47:19.375
No. Lidia. It's fine.

884
00:47:20.541 --> 00:47:23.000
Sweetie. go and sit next to Jacopo.

885
00:47:23.916 --> 00:47:24.916
Let's go.

886
00:47:37.166 --> 00:47:38.833
[Teresa chuckles uncomfortably]

887
00:47:38.916 --> 00:47:41.625
Your father looks very handsome
in full dress uniform.

888
00:47:44.250 --> 00:47:47.541
[Enrico] You know who called before lunch
to wish me a happy Easter. Lidia?

889
00:47:47.625 --> 00:47:48.750
[Lidia] Hm?

890
00:47:48.833 --> 00:47:50.541
- [Enrico] Zanardelli.
- [Lidia] Mm.

891
00:47:51.375 --> 00:47:55.791
[Enrico] The scandalmongers
paint him as a vulgar simpleton.

892
00:47:55.875 --> 00:47:58.083
but he's actually a delightful person.

893
00:47:59.958 --> 00:48:02.541
He hasn't expressed
a clear opinion on our law yet.

894
00:48:02.625 --> 00:48:04.791
but he promised me
that when he becomes Minister.

895
00:48:04.875 --> 00:48:07.500
he'll offer me a very important position.

896
00:48:07.583 --> 00:48:09.291
He already buried Depretis.

897
00:48:09.375 --> 00:48:11.250
[Grazia screams]

898
00:48:11.333 --> 00:48:13.541
[ominous music playing]

899
00:48:13.625 --> 00:48:14.500
[Lidia] Grazia!

900
00:48:14.583 --> 00:48:17.208
No. stay. sweetheart.
Stay right here. I'll be back.

901
00:48:27.583 --> 00:48:29.500
[Grazia panting]

902
00:48:31.208 --> 00:48:33.291
He just tried to kill me.

903
00:48:35.708 --> 00:48:38.083
["Misfit" by RIIVAL playing]

904
00:48:38.166 --> 00:48:40.666
<i>♪ I'm a misfit. I'm a misfit ♪</i>

905
00:48:40.750 --> 00:48:43.791
<i>♪ Yeah. I'm different</i>
<i>Yeah. I'm different ♪</i>

906
00:48:43.875 --> 00:48:46.375
<i>♪ You don't wanna miss this ♪</i>

907
00:48:46.458 --> 00:48:50.291
<i>♪ You're gonna wanna witness. whoa! ♪</i>

908
00:48:50.375 --> 00:48:53.375
<i>♪ Whoa! ♪</i>

909
00:48:54.500 --> 00:48:56.000
<i>♪ Whoa! ♪</i>

910
00:48:56.083 --> 00:48:59.041
<i>♪ Whoa! ♪</i>

911
00:49:02.000 --> 00:49:05.666
<i>♪ Whoa! ♪</i>

912
00:49:06.208 --> 00:49:07.291
<i>♪ Whoa! ♪</i>

913
00:49:07.833 --> 00:49:11.458
<i>♪ Whoa! ♪</i>

914
00:49:13.208 --> 00:49:15.958
<i>♪ You're gonna miss me when I'm gone ♪</i>

915
00:49:16.041 --> 00:49:18.875
<i>♪ But you can't have all the fun ♪</i>

916
00:49:18.958 --> 00:49:21.833
<i>♪ Gotta give everyone a taste ♪</i>

917
00:49:21.916 --> 00:49:24.791
<i>♪ Can't let my greatness go to waste ♪</i>

918
00:49:24.875 --> 00:49:27.875
<i>♪ So I'm flying state to state ♪</i>

919
00:49:27.958 --> 00:49:30.625
<i>♪ And they patiently await ♪</i>

920
00:49:31.208 --> 00:49:33.750
<i>♪ Everybody needs something to believe ♪</i>

921
00:49:33.833 --> 00:49:36.625
<i>♪ And that something might be me ♪</i>

922
00:49:36.708 --> 00:49:37.958
<i>♪ I'm a misfit ♪</i>

923
00:49:39.250 --> 00:49:41.625
<i>♪ Yeah. I'm different ♪</i>

924
00:49:42.208 --> 00:49:44.791
<i>♪ You don't wanna miss this ♪</i>

925
00:49:44.875 --> 00:49:48.166
<i>♪ You're gonna wanna witness. whoa! ♪</i>

926
00:49:48.250 --> 00:49:50.250
<i>♪ I'm a misfit ♪</i>

927
00:49:50.333 --> 00:49:52.625
[closing theme music playing]

928
